<h1>Nitin Khanna</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.nitinkhanna.com/now/">nitinkhanna.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Seattle
WA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Software Engineer at F5 Networks. I'm technically a Network Engineer, but I love python too much to bother with wires. :P
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I write what I can pull out of this mess of a brain and hope that someone somewhere will find coherence in that.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I am driven by a deep need to tell my story beyond my lifespan. It seems writing is the best way to do that.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Truth and dark chocolate are both bitter.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Adventures of Tintin by Herge and Johnathan Livingston Seagull by Richard Bach. Both taught me a lot about life and gave me my sense of adventure.
</p>

